The paper discusses the use of binary weights and activations for neural network acoustic models, which is related to topics such as model compression, hardware acceleration, and efficient neural network architectures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
